author: COMSOL
description: This example models time-dependent copper deposition on a resistive wafer in a cupplater reactor. As the deposited layer builds up, the resistive losses of the deposited layer decreases. The benefit of using a current thief for a more uniform deposit thickness is demonstrated.
label: resistive_wafer.mph
